quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  18,1,"All praise be to Allah Who has sent down upon His slave the Book, and has not allowed any crookedness therein"
  18,2,"an upright Book, to warn of a severe punishment from Him, and to give glad tidings to the believers who do righteous deeds, that they will have a good reward"
  18,3,wherein they will abide forever
  18,4,"and to warn those who say, “Allah has begotten a son.”"
  18,5,"They have no knowledge of it, nor did their forefathers. What a monstrous word that comes out of their mouths! They say nothing but lies"
  18,6,"Perhaps you grieve yourself to death [O Prophet] over them, if they do not believe in this message"
  18,7,"We have made all that is on earth as an adornment for it, so that We may test them as to which of them is best in deeds"
  18,8,And We will surely turn all that is on it to a barren land
  18,9,Do you think that the people of the Cave and the Inscription were of Our only wondrous signs
  18,10,"When the youths took refuge in the Cave, and said, “Our Lord, grant us mercy from Yourself, and show us the right way in our ordeal.”"
  18,11,Then We caused them to fall into a deep sleep in the cave for many years
  18,12,Then We awakened them so that We may see which of the two parties would be more precise in calculating the length of their stay